-- GE's North American retail finance business files for IPO
-- By Aman Shah in Bangalore
-- Thu Mar 13, 2014 07:14AM EDT
-- None



March 13 (Reuters) - General Electric Co's <GE.N> North American retail finance business filed with U.S. regulators to raise up to $100 million in an initial public offering of common stock.

The business will operate under a new name, Synchrony Financial, GE said in a statement. [ID:nBw6wCjhFa] Goldman Sachs & Co, JP Morgan, Citigroup and Morgan Stanley are lead underwriters for the IPO, Synchrony's filing showed. (http://r.reuters.com/hez57v)